div",{className:"flex items-center justify-end gap-3 p-6",children:[m.jsx("button",{onClick:()=>e(xp()),className:"bg-[#EEF0F4] text-[#586A84] hover:bg-[#7D8FA9] hover:text-[#FFFFFF] px-3 py-2 rounded-md cursor-pointer",children:"Close"}),m.jsx("button",{type:"submit",className:"bg-[#292929] text-white px-3 py-2 rounded-md cursor-pointer hover:bg-[#F5F5F5] hover:text-[#3D207E]",children:i!=null&&i.github_link?"Update URLs":"Submit URLs"})]})]})})})]})},G_=[{question:"I have registered but have not received my offer letter yet. When will I get access to my offer letter and the learning/project portal?",answer:"Don't worry! You will receive your offer letter and access to the registration portal on your batch starting date. We appreciate your patience and thank you for waiting!",role:"OfferLetter"},{question:"I have completed the registration. What is the next process?",answer:`
        Welcome to Unified Mentor! 🎉 We are thrilled that you have decided to join the Unified Team. Your offer letter is on its way and will arrive in your inbox shortly. We will send it to you via email for your convenience.
  Exciting news! All the details for your induction session, including the time and link, will be included in your offer letter. It’s going to be an enlightening experience you won’t want to miss!
  Mark your calendar, as you will receive access to the portal on the day your batch starts. Your patience during this process is   greatly appreciated. Thank you for becoming a valued member of our team! 🌟`,role:"OfferLetter"},{question:"What should I do if I did not receive the offer letter or other information after the batch started?",answer:`If you have not received your offer letter or other important information after your batch has started, please follow these steps:
  Firstly, check your spam and promotional folders. Sometimes, important emails can end up in these folders. Please ensure that the email wasn't misclassified and is not sitting in one of these folders.
  If you still can't find the email, please contact our support team for assistance. We are here to help and will make sure you receive all the necessary information.
  Thank you for your understanding and patience!
  `,role:"OfferLetter"},{question:"My UNID is not shown. What should I do?",answer:"Your UNID is already mentioned in the offer letter. Please check your offer letter for this information. If you still cannot find it, feel free to reach out to our support team for further assistance.",role:"OfferLetter"},{question:"Where should I submit my assignment?",answer:"Assignments are provided for learning purposes and practice only. You do not need to submit them. Feel free to work on them to enhance your understanding and skills.",role:"Assignment"},{question:"I can work on basic projects but am having difficulty with advanced projects. What should I do?",answer:"You can work on projects according to your skill level and choice. If you find advanced projects challenging, it's perfectly fine to focus on basic projects. You can gradually progress to more advanced ones as you build your skills and confidence. Feel free to choose projects that match your current abilities and interests.",role:"Assignment"},{question:"I am unable to submit my projects on time. Can you extend my deadline for project completion?",answer:"Yes, we can grant you extra time to complete your projects. Please let us know your new proposed deadline, and we will make the necessary adjustments to accommodate it. We want to ensure you have ample time to complete your work.",role:"Assignment"},{question:"My submission link is not working or active. What should I do?",answer:"Please use the following link to submit your project: Submit Your Project(https://forms.gle/HdV9Qr6j2iH2jm34A) Here. If you encounter any issues with the link or need further assistance, feel free to reach out to us. We're here to help and ensure your submission phase is successful!",role:"Assignment"},{question:"My chapters are locked. When will they be unlocked?",answer:"Chapters will be unlocked on a day-by-day basis according to the course schedule. Please check back regularly to see when new chapters become available. Thank you for your patience!",role:"Assignment"},{question:"When will I receive my certificates?",answer:"You will receive your certificates after completing the internship phase. Once the internship is finished and all requirements are met, we will issue your certificates. Thank you for your patience!",role:"Certificate"},{question:"I have completed my internship but have not received my certificates yet. What should I do?",answer:"Please ensure that you have submitted all your projects. Certificates are issued after the successful completion of the internship and the submission of all required projects. If you have already submitted your projects and still haven't received your certificate, please contact our support team for further assistance.",role:"Certificate"},{question:"When will I get access to the portal?",answer:"Don't worry! You will receive access to the portal on your batch starting date. Thanks for waiting!",role:"PortalAccess"},{question:"I have taken the Data Science course, but the Data Analyst course is visible to me. What should I do?",answer:"Don't worry, The Data Analyst projects are included within the Data Science course. You can select and work on them as part of your course. If you still have any confusion, you can also add your own projects and work on them. Feel free to choose any project of your choice or add any project from your side. Thank you for your understanding.",role:"PortalAccess"},{question:"I am not able to see the video content for Web Development; instead, I can only see the text content. Why is that?",answer:"Don't worry! Currently, only the text content is available for the Web Development section, as it covers basic knowledge. For now, you can use the available text content to gain the necessary understanding. If you have any specific questions or need further assistance, feel free to reach out.",role:"PortalAccess"},{question:"I have taken the 3-month plan, but we only have 30 chapters. Why is that?",answer:"The 30 chapters you see are designed to cover the core learning modules for the first 30 days of the plan. After completing these modules, you will enter a self-paced internship phase for the remaining duration of the 3-month plan. During this internship, you will apply what you've learned and gain practical experience.",role:"PortalAccess"},{question:"There are no live classes, and I have not received a mentor yet. What should I do?",answer:"In this plan, mentor assistance is not included. You will need to work on your projects independently. However, if you encounter any issues or have questions, you can message me through the query portal. I will do my best to address your queries and respond as soon as possible.",role:"PortalAccess"}],koe={openfaqIndex:null,userResponse:"",activeState:"OfferLetter"},Zq=hi({name:"faqs",initialState:koe,reducers:{setActiveState:(e,t)=>{e.activeState=e.activeState===t.payload?"":t.payload},sethandleFaq:(e,t)=>{e.openfaqIndex=e.openfaqIndex===t.payload?null:t.payload},setUserResponse:(e,t)=>{e.userResponse=t.payload}}}),{setActiveState:Doe,sethandleFaq:Toe,setUserResponse:Poe}=Zq.actions,Roe=Zq.reducer,XT=P.createContext({});function QT(e){const t=P.useRef(null);return t.current===null&&(t.current=e()),t.current}const JT=typeof window<"u",e7=JT?P.useLayoutEffect:P.useEffect,tw=P.createContext(null),ZT=P.createContext({transformPagePoint:e=>e,isStatic:!1,reducedMotion:"never"});class Moe extends P.Component{getSnapshotBeforeUpdate(t){const n=this.props.childRef.current;if(n&&t.isPresent&&!this.props.isPresent){const i=n.offsetParent,r=i instanceof HTMLElement&&i.offsetWidth||0,a=this.props.sizeRef.current;a.height=n.offsetHeight||0,a.width=n.offsetWidth||0,a.top=n.offsetTop,a.left=n.offsetLeft,a.right=r-a.width-a.left}return null}componentDidUpdate(){}render(){return this.props.children}}function Ooe({children:e,isPresent:t,anchorX:n}){const i=P.useId(),r=P.useRef(null),a=P.useRef({width:0,height:0,top:0,left:0,right:0}),{nonce:s}=P.useContext(ZT);return P